Large-scale real estate scandals in Quebec
Officials of the road department, companies in the construction industry, fundraisers of political parties and specialists of the Italian mafia tell every day what they know about a great "system" in which the construction industry, civil servants, politicians, trade unionists and mafioso are involved.
An "industry" that was very expensive for Quebec taxpayers, especially in the 1990s and 2000s.
"It's strange how the system has fallen apart since drastic measures were taken," jokes Jacques Duchesneau, a Quebec congressman and former head of the Montreal Police Department.
The scandal was uncovered by him as a result of an in-depth investigation into the embezzlement in connection with the contracts for road works in Quebec, which the then Prime Minister had only reluctantly agreed.
The "Duchesneau Report" established a direct link between industry, secret party funding and bribery of officials.
"Since the investigation began in 2010," he points out, "the Department of Transportation alone has saved a billion dollars on contracts," because some have curbed their instinct to get their share!
