These funds were used to acquire shares in the Administradora Profesional de Hoteles (the professional hotel management).
As you know, Azcárraga Andrade is the main shareholder of the Posadas hotel chain.
Dragon Mart is surrounded
At a weekend meeting at a University of the Caribbean forum, a group of national and foreign environmentalists, academics, entrepreneurs and general members of civil society decided to create a broad front to oppose the opening of China's Dragon Mart in Cancún.
As you know, we are talking about a huge sales and distribution center in Mexico, Central America and the Caribbean with products from the land beyond the wall, supplemented by a living area for the employees of 150 companies.
In the run-up, the Canacintra (the National Chamber of Manufacturing Industries) has managed to unite the governors in the southeast to oppose the monumental institution, which destroyed partially protected areas and is the mother of all threats to industry.
ACTA is dead
Because the government did not comply with a request from the Senate to explain under what conditions and circumstances the Mexican ambassador to Japan signed the Anti-Counterfeiting Trade Agreement, known by its acronym ACTA, the matter has already been archived, according to the Mexican Institute of Intellectual Property.
As you know, these measures were taken despite the fact that the Senate had disconsidered the possibility because it considered it a violation of freedom of expression on social networks.
Homex long-term
In pursuit of paying long-term liabilities without affecting short-term liabilities, construction company Homex is launching stock exchange certificates worth over 500 million pesos.
The issue is the first of four identical issuances that promise to pay interest every 28 days.
Foundation of Competival
